28#ifndef _SYS_ACL_H
29#define _SYS_ACL_H
30
31#include <sys/types.h>
32#include <sys/acl_impl.h>
33
34#ifdef __cplusplus
35extern "C" {
36#endif
37
38#define MAX_ACL_ENTRIES (1024) /* max entries of each type */
39typedef struct {
40 int a_type; /* the type of ACL entry */
41 uid_t a_id; /* the entry in -uid or gid */
42 o_mode_t a_perm; /* the permission field */
43} aclent_t;
44
45typedef struct ace {
46 uid_t a_who; /* uid or gid */
47 uint32_t a_access_mask; /* read,write,... */
48 uint16_t a_flags; /* see below */
49 uint16_t a_type; /* allow or deny */
50} ace_t;
51
52#ifndef _KERNEL
53typedef struct acl_info acl_t;
54#endif
55
56/*
57 * The following are Defined types for an aclent_t.
58 */
59#define USER_OBJ (0x01) /* object owner */
60#define USER (0x02) /* additional users */
61#define GROUP_OBJ (0x04) /* owning group of the object */
62#define GROUP (0x08) /* additional groups */
63#define CLASS_OBJ (0x10) /* file group class and mask entry */
64#define OTHER_OBJ (0x20) /* other entry for the object */
65#define ACL_DEFAULT (0x1000) /* default flag */
66/* default object owner */
67#define DEF_USER_OBJ (ACL_DEFAULT | USER_OBJ)
68/* default additional users */
69#define DEF_USER (ACL_DEFAULT | USER)
70/* default owning group */
71#define DEF_GROUP_OBJ (ACL_DEFAULT | GROUP_OBJ)
72/* default additional groups */
73#define DEF_GROUP (ACL_DEFAULT | GROUP)
74/* default mask entry */
75#define DEF_CLASS_OBJ (ACL_DEFAULT | CLASS_OBJ)
76/* default other entry */
77#define DEF_OTHER_OBJ (ACL_DEFAULT | OTHER_OBJ)
78
79/*
80 * The following are defined for ace_t.
81 */
82#define ACE_READ_DATA 0x00000001
83#define ACE_LIST_DIRECTORY 0x00000001
84#define ACE_WRITE_DATA 0x00000002
85#define ACE_ADD_FILE 0x00000002
86#define ACE_APPEND_DATA 0x00000004
87#define ACE_ADD_SUBDIRECTORY 0x00000004
88#define ACE_READ_NAMED_ATTRS 0x00000008
89#define ACE_WRITE_NAMED_ATTRS 0x00000010
90#define ACE_EXECUTE 0x00000020
91#define ACE_DELETE_CHILD 0x00000040
92#define ACE_READ_ATTRIBUTES 0x00000080
93#define ACE_WRITE_ATTRIBUTES 0x00000100
94#define ACE_DELETE 0x00010000
95#define ACE_READ_ACL 0x00020000
96#define ACE_WRITE_ACL 0x00040000
97#define ACE_WRITE_OWNER 0x00080000
98#define ACE_SYNCHRONIZE 0x00100000
99
100#define ACE_FILE_INHERIT_ACE 0x0001
101#define ACE_DIRECTORY_INHERIT_ACE 0x0002
102#define ACE_NO_PROPAGATE_INHERIT_ACE 0x0004
103#define ACE_INHERIT_ONLY_ACE 0x0008
104#define ACE_SUCCESSFUL_ACCESS_ACE_FLAG 0x0010
105#define ACE_FAILED_ACCESS_ACE_FLAG 0x0020
106#define ACE_IDENTIFIER_GROUP 0x0040
107#define ACE_INHERITED_ACE 0x0080
108#define ACE_OWNER 0x1000
109#define ACE_GROUP 0x2000
110#define ACE_EVERYONE 0x4000
111
112#define ACE_ACCESS_ALLOWED_ACE_TYPE 0x0000
113#define ACE_ACCESS_DENIED_ACE_TYPE 0x0001
114#define ACE_SYSTEM_AUDIT_ACE_TYPE 0x0002
115#define ACE_SYSTEM_ALARM_ACE_TYPE 0x0003
116
117#define ACL_AUTO_INHERIT 0x0001
118#define ACL_PROTECTED 0x0002
119#define ACL_DEFAULTED 0x0004
120#define ACL_FLAGS_ALL (ACL_AUTO_INHERIT|ACL_PROTECTED| \
121 ACL_DEFAULTED)
122
123#ifdef _KERNEL
124
125/*
126 * These are only applicable in a CIFS context.
127 */
128#define ACE_ACCESS_ALLOWED_COMPOUND_ACE_TYPE 0x04
129#define ACE_ACCESS_ALLOWED_OBJECT_ACE_TYPE 0x05
130#define ACE_ACCESS_DENIED_OBJECT_ACE_TYPE 0x06
131#define ACE_SYSTEM_AUDIT_OBJECT_ACE_TYPE 0x07
132#define ACE_SYSTEM_ALARM_OBJECT_ACE_TYPE 0x08
133#define ACE_ACCESS_ALLOWED_CALLBACK_ACE_TYPE 0x09
134#define ACE_ACCESS_DENIED_CALLBACK_ACE_TYPE 0x0A
135#define ACE_ACCESS_ALLOWED_CALLBACK_OBJECT_ACE_TYPE 0x0B
136#define ACE_ACCESS_DENIED_CALLBACK_OBJECT_ACE_TYPE 0x0C
137#define ACE_SYSTEM_AUDIT_CALLBACK_ACE_TYPE 0x0D
138#define ACE_SYSTEM_ALARM_CALLBACK_ACE_TYPE 0x0E
139#define ACE_SYSTEM_AUDIT_CALLBACK_OBJECT_ACE_TYPE 0x0F
140#define ACE_SYSTEM_ALARM_CALLBACK_OBJECT_ACE_TYPE 0x10
141
142#define ACE_ALL_TYPES 0x001F
143
144typedef struct ace_object {
145 uid_t a_who; /* uid or gid */
146 uint32_t a_access_mask; /* read,write,... */
147 uint16_t a_flags; /* see below */
148 uint16_t a_type; /* allow or deny */
149 uint8_t a_obj_type[16]; /* obj type */
150 uint8_t a_inherit_obj_type[16]; /* inherit obj */
151} ace_object_t;
152
153#endif
154
155#define ACE_ALL_PERMS (ACE_READ_DATA|ACE_LIST_DIRECTORY|ACE_WRITE_DATA| \
156 ACE_ADD_FILE|ACE_APPEND_DATA|ACE_ADD_SUBDIRECTORY|ACE_READ_NAMED_ATTRS| \
157 ACE_WRITE_NAMED_ATTRS|ACE_EXECUTE|ACE_DELETE_CHILD|ACE_READ_ATTRIBUTES| \
158 ACE_WRITE_ATTRIBUTES|ACE_DELETE|ACE_READ_ACL|ACE_WRITE_ACL| \
159 ACE_WRITE_OWNER|ACE_SYNCHRONIZE)
160
161#define ACE_ALL_WRITE_PERMS (ACE_WRITE_DATA|ACE_APPEND_DATA| \
162 ACE_WRITE_ATTRIBUTES|ACE_WRITE_NAMED_ATTRS|ACE_WRITE_ACL| \
163 ACE_WRITE_OWNER|ACE_DELETE|ACE_DELETE_CHILD)
164
165#define ACE_READ_PERMS (ACE_READ_DATA|ACE_READ_ACL|ACE_READ_ATTRIBUTES| \
166 ACE_READ_NAMED_ATTRS)
167
168#define ACE_WRITE_PERMS (ACE_WRITE_DATA|ACE_APPEND_DATA|ACE_WRITE_ATTRIBUTES| \
169 ACE_WRITE_NAMED_ATTRS)
170
171#define ACE_MODIFY_PERMS (ACE_READ_DATA|ACE_LIST_DIRECTORY|ACE_WRITE_DATA| \
172 ACE_ADD_FILE|ACE_APPEND_DATA|ACE_ADD_SUBDIRECTORY|ACE_READ_NAMED_ATTRS| \
173 ACE_WRITE_NAMED_ATTRS|ACE_EXECUTE|ACE_DELETE_CHILD|ACE_READ_ATTRIBUTES| \
174 ACE_WRITE_ATTRIBUTES|ACE_DELETE|ACE_READ_ACL|ACE_SYNCHRONIZE)
175/*
176 * The following flags are supported by both NFSv4 ACLs and ace_t.
177 */
178#define ACE_NFSV4_SUP_FLAGS (ACE_FILE_INHERIT_ACE | \
179 ACE_DIRECTORY_INHERIT_ACE | \
180 ACE_NO_PROPAGATE_INHERIT_ACE | \
181 ACE_INHERIT_ONLY_ACE | \
182 ACE_INHERITED_ACE | \
183 ACE_IDENTIFIER_GROUP)
184
185#define ACE_TYPE_FLAGS (ACE_OWNER|ACE_GROUP|ACE_EVERYONE| \
186 ACE_IDENTIFIER_GROUP)
187#define ACE_INHERIT_FLAGS (ACE_FILE_INHERIT_ACE| ACL_INHERITED_ACE| \
188 ACE_DIRECTORY_INHERIT_ACE|ACE_NO_PROPAGATE_INHERIT_ACE|ACE_INHERIT_ONLY_ACE)
189
190/* cmd args to acl(2) for aclent_t */
191#define GETACL 1
192#define SETACL 2
193#define GETACLCNT 3
194
195/* cmd's to manipulate ace acls. */
196#define ACE_GETACL 4
197#define ACE_SETACL 5
198#define ACE_GETACLCNT 6
199
200/* minimal acl entries from GETACLCNT */
201#define MIN_ACL_ENTRIES 4

205/* acl check errors */
206#define GRP_ERROR 1
207#define USER_ERROR 2
208#define OTHER_ERROR 3
209#define CLASS_ERROR 4
210#define DUPLICATE_ERROR 5
211#define MISS_ERROR 6
212#define MEM_ERROR 7
213#define ENTRY_ERROR 8
214

216/*
217 * similar to ufs_acl.h: changed to char type for user commands (tar, cpio)
218 * Attribute types
219 */
220#define UFSD_FREE ('0') /* Free entry */
221#define UFSD_ACL ('1') /* Access Control Lists */
222#define UFSD_DFACL ('2') /* reserved for future use */
223#define ACE_ACL ('3') /* ace_t style acls */
224
225/*
226 * flag to [f]acl_get()
227 * controls whether a trivial acl should be returned.
228 */
229#define ACL_NO_TRIVIAL 0x2
230
231
232/*
233 * Flags to control acl_totext()
234 */
235
236#define ACL_APPEND_ID 0x1 /* append uid/gid to user/group entries */
237#define ACL_COMPACT_FMT 0x2 /* build ACL in ls -V format */
238#define ACL_NORESOLVE 0x4 /* don't do name service lookups */
239#define ACL_SID_FMT 0x8 /* use usersid/groupsid when appropriate */
240
241/*
242 * Legacy aclcheck errors for aclent_t ACLs
243 */
244#define EACL_GRP_ERROR GRP_ERROR
245#define EACL_USER_ERROR USER_ERROR
246#define EACL_OTHER_ERROR OTHER_ERROR
247#define EACL_CLASS_ERROR CLASS_ERROR
248#define EACL_DUPLICATE_ERROR DUPLICATE_ERROR
249#define EACL_MISS_ERROR MISS_ERROR
250#define EACL_MEM_ERROR MEM_ERROR
251#define EACL_ENTRY_ERROR ENTRY_ERROR
252
253#define EACL_INHERIT_ERROR 9 /* invalid inherit flags */
254#define EACL_FLAGS_ERROR 10 /* unknown flag value */
255#define EACL_PERM_MASK_ERROR 11 /* unknown permission */
256#define EACL_COUNT_ERROR 12 /* invalid acl count */
257
258#define EACL_INVALID_SLOT 13 /* invalid acl slot */
259#define EACL_NO_ACL_ENTRY 14 /* Entry doesn't exist */
260#define EACL_DIFF_TYPE 15 /* acls aren't same type */
261
262#define EACL_INVALID_USER_GROUP 16 /* need user/group name */
263#define EACL_INVALID_STR 17 /* invalid acl string */
264#define EACL_FIELD_NOT_BLANK 18 /* can't have blank field */
265#define EACL_INVALID_ACCESS_TYPE 19 /* invalid access type */
266#define EACL_UNKNOWN_DATA 20 /* Unrecognized data in ACL */
267#define EACL_MISSING_FIELDS 21 /* missing fields in acl */
268
269#define EACL_INHERIT_NOTDIR 22 /* Need dir for inheritance */

288#else /* !defined(_KERNEL) */
